The paper deals with visual object tracking, which is a fundamental task in computer vision, and proposes a new Siamese network architecture called DomainSiam that improves feature learning and generalization capability to other domains. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a new loss function to solve the sparsity problem, which involves optimization and machine learning techniques, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely category. The paper also utilizes pre-trained networks and semantic information, which are related to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The experiments involve tracking benchmarks, which are related to cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the paper deals with tracking, which is related to cs.RO (Robotics).
